      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Clarkson's Farm article CTR fix</h3>
      <p>
        <code>/articles/valais-blacknose-sheep</code> is ranking position 7–8 on page 1 for ten Jeremy Clarkson sheep-breed queries (112 impressions in 28 days) with zero clicks. The old title led with "Valais Blacknose Sheep" — but the real search intent is "what breed are Jeremy Clarkson's sheep." Rewrote the title and meta description to front-load Clarkson's name and the "faceless sheep" nickname users actually type. Position is already there; this is purely a click-magnet rewrite to convert impressions into traffic.
      </p>
